{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"0948e400-c035-4ef6-88ed-4974f5285631","content":"Two things change with xUnit v3 + MTP:\n\n### 1. Filter syntax\n\nVSTest used `&` for AND. MTP uses `--filter` with a different expression syntax:\n\n```bash\n# Old (VSTest / xUnit v2)\ndotnet test --filter \"FullyQualifiedName~IntegrationTests&Category=Smoke\"\n\n# New (MTP / xUnit v3)\ndotnet test --filter \"FullyQualifiedName~IntegrationTests and trait=Category%3DSmoke\"\n```\n\nKey differences:\n- **`&`** → **`and`** (logical operator is a keyword, not `&`)\n- **`Category=Smoke`** → **`trait=Category%3DSmoke`** — xUnit v3 on MTP exposes traits via a single `trait` property using `Key=Value` format (`%3D` is the URL-encoded `=`)\n\n### 2. Runner package\n\nYour `.csproj` sets `UseMicrosoftTestingPlatformRunner` but is missing the MTP runner package. Add it:\n\n```xml\n<PackageReference Include=\"xunit.runner.mtp\" Version=\"1.0.1\" />\n```\n\n### Quick reference\n\n| Concept | VSTest filter | MTP filter |\n|---|---|---|\n| Name contains | `FullyQualifiedName~Foo` | `FullyQualifiedName~Foo` |\n| Trait match | `Category=Smoke` | `trait=Category%3DSmoke` |\n| AND | `&` | `and` |\n| OR | `\\|` | `or` |","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"2fbcf976-a710-4984-b99b-a7a5db9c574f","outputTokens":390,"requestId":"083A:16A6CA:7F7C7B5:8DB92B2:69EABF55"},"id":"9ba3ed44-ffb4-4f13-872e-5c674c910c6f","timestamp":"2026-04-24T00:54:53.469Z","parentId":"32e93fe5-84a5-4ea8-8b10-b3114dd67061"}
